## Annual meeting

Do we need to get voting going now?  Does our voting software work?  When do we
need to start taking nominations?

Strictly speaking nominations is July 1-14, voting 15-28, swearing in the 29th

Annual board member elections take place at annual meeting and are governed by
[resolution 2004-08-10.dbg.2](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.dbg.2/)

Nominations take place from July 1st to 14th, with voting taking place from
July 15th to 28th. Voting takes place using Condorcet/SSD, an explanation of
which can be found at:

http://people.debian.org/~branden/talks/condorcet_and_debian/

At the 2006 board meeting, the seats of Bruce Perens, Benj. Mako Hill, and John
Goerzen will be up for election.

